# Flyway — schema changes (production deployed)

**Learn (Cursos) has a deployed baseline** (`V1.0.0`). Do **not** rewrite shipped migrations.

## Rule

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| New/changed table or column | Add the next versioned file under `src/main/resources/db/migration/` (e.g. `V1.0.1__…`, `V1.0.2__…`) |
| Data backfill | Include in the same migration (or a follow-up version) with safe `INSERT … SELECT` / `UPDATE` |
| Shipped files | **Never** edit `V1.0.0__Database_Creation.sql` or any already-applied migration on production |

## Same PR checklist

1. Add `V1.x.y__Descriptive_Name.sql` with forward-only DDL/DML.
2. Update [`dev-import.sql`](../../src/main/resources/dev-import.sql) for the **current** schema after all migrations — see [dev-import-sql-safety.mdc](dev-import-sql-safety.mdc).
3. Update JPA entities to match.
4. Run `mvn test` (Flyway runs on `@QuarkusTest` startup; `%dev` clean-at-start applies the full chain).

## Examples

```sql
-- ✅ Production: new versioned migration
-- V1.0.1__Aula_Blocks.sql
CREATE TABLE tb_aula_blocks ( ... );
INSERT INTO tb_aula_blocks (...)
SELECT ... FROM tb_course_items;
ALTER TABLE tb_course_items DROP COLUMN ...;
```

```sql
-- ❌ Do not amend shipped baseline for live DBs
-- (editing V1.0.0__Database_Creation.sql)
```

## Never

- Bypass Flyway — schema lives under `src/main/resources/db/migration/`.
- Edit or delete a migration that may already be applied in production.
- Rely on `dev-import.sql` alone for schema shape.
